cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with scheduling in a wireless-powered IoT system, which involves communication, networking, and information theory aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves channel modeling and analysis, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory). The system design and optimization aspects can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves signal processing and communication aspects, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with security and privacy aspects of wireless communication, which can be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
